<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
<title>multicol | column-rule-style</title>
<link rel="author" title="Hakon Wium Lie" href="mailto:howcome@opera.com"/>
<style type="text/css">
div, table {
  font: 50px/50px Ahem;
  width: 410px;
  margin: 10px 0;
  color: black;
  background: black;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  orphans: 1;
  widows: 1;
}

td { border-right: 10px outset lime; padding: 0 }
td + td { border-left: 10px outset lime; border-right: none }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<p>The two horizontal bars should look the same.</p>
<table><tr><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr></table>
<table><tr><td>0</td><td>0</td></tr></table>
</body>
</html>
